\title{R6 class for medical condition code specifications}
\description{
Stores the code sets and narrative algorithm description for a single
version of a medical condition definition. Each version is a distinct
object (e.g., \code{spec_htn_v1}, \code{spec_htn_v2}).

The spec stores:
\itemize{
\item \code{defs}: named list with elements \code{condition} and \code{outcome}, each holding
a narrative algorithm description string (or \code{NULL} if not defined).
\item \code{codes}: named list of key-level lists keyed by \verb{\{code_type\}_\{encounter\}}
(e.g., \code{dx_icd9}). Each key-level list has:
\itemize{
\item \code{codes}: character vector of exact short-format codes (no periods).
\item \code{condition}: logical vector parallel to \code{codes}; \code{TRUE} if the code
belongs to the condition/history definition.
\item \code{outcome}: logical vector parallel to \code{codes}; \code{TRUE} if the code
belongs to the outcome definition.
\item \code{exclusions}: optional character string describing codes to exclude.
}
}
}
